## Testing Strategy

### Unit Tests — `test/lib/seer-trial.test.ts`
- `isTrialEligibleError`: returns true for `no_budget`/`not_enabled` with orgSlug + TTY, false for `ai_disabled`, false without orgSlug, false for non-SeerError
- `promptAndStartSeerTrial`: mock `getSeerTrialStatus` + `startSeerTrial` + `log.prompt`
  - Trial available + user confirms → starts trial, returns true
  - Trial available + user declines → returns false, no API call
  - Trial available + user cancels (Ctrl+C Symbol) → returns false
  - No trial available → returns false immediately (no prompt)
  - `getSeerTrialStatus` throws → returns false (graceful degradation)
  - `startSeerTrial` throws → returns false, warns user

### Unit Tests — `test/lib/api-client.seer-trial.test.ts`
- `getSeerTrialStatus`: mock fetch for customer endpoint
  - Returns seerUsers trial when available (unstarted)
  - Prefers seerUsers over seerAutofix
  - Returns null when no trials
  - Returns null when all trials started
- `startSeerTrial`: mock fetch for product-trial endpoint
  - Sends correct PUT request body
  - Throws on API error

